 12  /-!
 13  # Submonoids
 14  
 15  This file defines multiplicative and additive submonoids, first in an unbundled form (deprecated)
 16  and then in a bundled form.
 17  
 18  We prove submonoids of a monoid form a complete lattice, and results about images and preimages of
 19  submonoids under monoid homomorphisms. For the unbundled submonoids, these theorems use unbundled
 20  monoid homomorphisms (also deprecated), and the bundled versions use bundled monoid homomorphisms.
 21  
 22  There are also theorems about the submonoids generated by an element or a subset of a monoid,
 23  defined both inductively and as the infimum of the set of submonoids containing a given
 24  element/subset.
 25  
 26  ## Implementation notes
 27  
 28  Unbundled submonoids will slowly be removed from mathlib.
 29  
 30  (Bundled) submonoid inclusion is denoted `≤` rather than `⊆`, although `∈` is defined as
 31  membership of a submonoid's underlying set.
 32  
 33  ## Tags
 34  submonoid, submonoids, is_submonoid
 35  -/
